# LapyTrack — Core Project Rules

## Scope
- **Only work inside `krish-computer-app/`**. This is the sole active app (LapyTrack / Krish Computer Store Manager).
- **Do not** use or reference legacy folders at the workspace parent: `DayBook-Tracker/`, `INward-outward/` (removed; were old prototypes).
- **Git repo:** https://github.com/kforkreativein/lapytrack (branch `main`)

## What the app is
- Laptop repair shop manager: device inward/outward, job sheets + QR codes, khata ledger, reports, customize catalog
- **Live frontend:** https://lapy-track.vercel.app
- **Live backend:** https://lapytrack.onrender.com
- **Database:** MongoDB Atlas, db name `krish_computer_db`

## Stack
| Layer | Tech | Location |
|-------|------|----------|
| Frontend | React 19, CRA+Craco, Tailwind, Shadcn, React Query, yarn | `frontend/` |
| Backend | FastAPI, Motor, Uvicorn, single `server.py` | `backend/` |
| Auth | 4-digit PIN (daily) + email/password (full login); JWT httponly cookie 7 days | `backend/server.py`, `frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx` |

## Before changing code
1. Read surrounding files; match existing patterns (minimal diffs)
2. Never commit `.env`, secrets, or `CLOUD.md` (local-only, gitignored)
3. Use **yarn** in frontend (not npm) — `packageManager` is yarn
4. Frontend env var: `REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL` (Vercel Production)
5. QR codes and job links must use `https://lapy-track.vercel.app`, never `localhost` in production

## Vercel (important)
- **Use project `frontend` only** — root dir `frontend/`, alias `lapy-track.vercel.app`
- **Never** create a second Vercel project from repo root (causes duplicate GitHub checks)

## Data persistence
- **MongoDB:** devices, customers, ledger, auth — persistent
- **Render disk (`backend/uploads/`):** photos are **ephemeral** on free tier (lost on redeploy). Prefer cloud storage for permanent images (future work)
